
PDFium
    PDFium is an open-source PDF rendering engine and library developed by Google, 
    primarily known for its use in Google Chrome and other applications.

    PDFium is primarily written in C++, and its core functionality is exposed through C++ APIs. 

Key Features and Capabilities:
    PDF Rendering
    Text and Image Extraction
    PDF Creation and Manipulation
    Form Handling
    JavaScript Support
    Open Source

Use Cases:
    Web Browsers
    Document Viewers and Editors
    Applications Needing PDF Functionality

URL:
    https://pdfium.googlesource.com/pdfium/


============================================================================
Prebuilt PDFium from GitHub

https://github.com/bblanchon/pdfium-binaries?tab=readme-ov-file

Tested on ubuntu 18 -->

1. download "pdfium-linux-x64.tgz"

from  https://github.com/bblanchon/pdfium-binaries/releases/latest/download/pdfium-linux-x64.tgz

2. extract pdfium-linux-x64.tgz 

3. and copy lib and inlcude dir from extract file to your project

4. done
----------------------------------------------------------------
📦 Install ImageMagick (if not installed):

sudo apt install imagemagick

🔁 Convert:

convert page0.ppm page0.png

Or for higher quality (optional):

convert page0.ppm -quality 100 page0.png
